service: Provides APIs for creating and managing SageMaker geospatial resources.

operations.DeleteEarthObservationJob: Use this operation to delete an Earth Observation job.
operations.DeleteVectorEnrichmentJob: Use this operation to delete a Vector Enrichment job.
operations.ExportEarthObservationJob: Use this operation to export results of an Earth Observation job and optionally source images used as input to the EOJ to an S3 location.
operations.ExportVectorEnrichmentJob: Use this operation to copy results of a Vector Enrichment job to an S3 location.
operations.GetEarthObservationJob: Get the details for a previously initiated Earth Observation job.
operations.GetRasterDataCollection: Use this operation to get details of a specific raster data collection.
operations.GetTile: Gets a web mercator tile for the given Earth Observation job.
operations.GetVectorEnrichmentJob: Retrieves details of a Vector Enrichment Job for a given job Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
operations.ListEarthObservationJobs: Use this operation to get a list of the Earth Observation jobs associated with the calling Amazon Web Services account.
operations.ListRasterDataCollections: Use this operation to get raster data collections.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Lists the tags attached to the resource.
operations.ListVectorEnrichmentJobs: Retrieves a list of vector enrichment jobs.
operations.SearchRasterDataCollection: Allows you run image query on a specific raster data collection to get a list of the satellite imagery matching the selected filters.
operations.StartEarthObservationJob: Use this operation to create an Earth observation job.
operations.StartVectorEnrichmentJob: Creates a Vector Enrichment job for the supplied job type. Currently, there are two supported job types: reverse geocoding and map matching.
operations.StopEarthObservationJob: Use this operation to stop an existing earth observation job.
operations.StopVectorEnrichmentJob: Stops the Vector Enrichment job for a given job ARN.
